<div id="review_2350776" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2350776" />
    <a title="Celia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/151499-celia"><img alt="Celia" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2350776?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Celia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Celia" href="/user/show/151499-celia">Celia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">ABSOLUTELY</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2350776" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2671517956844418493">If you want to know how to actually live in the present moment, then this book is for you<br/>I have become more midnful of my thoughts and actions, and the amount of time I spend daydreaming or assuming what someone or something else&apos;s reality is. Instead, I allow those thoughts to pass quickly, without judgement, and come back to the present, whatever it is I am doing that moment be it playing peek-a-boo with my son, cooking a meal, having a talk with my husband or friend or running a few miles.</span>
  <span id="freeText2671517956844418493" style="display:none">If you want to know how to actually live in the present moment, then this book is for you<br />I have become more midnful of my thoughts and actions, and the amount of time I spend daydreaming or assuming what someone or something else's reality is. Instead, I allow those thoughts to pass quickly, without judgement, and come back to the present, whatever it is I am doing that moment be it playing peek-a-boo with my son, cooking a meal, having a talk with my husband or friend or running a few miles.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2671517956844418493" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
